  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "RMVB = RealMedia VBR, same RMFF container as .rm. Magic '.RMF'(4B)+size(4B BE)+ver(2B BE)+fileVer(4B BE)+numHeaders(4B BE). At offset 18: PROP object ('PROP'+size+ver+maxBitRate+avgBitRate+maxPacketSize+avgPacketSize+numPackets+duration+preroll+indexOffset+dataOffset+numStreams+flags). VBR indicated by avgBitRate << maxBitRate in PROP. MDPR per stream contains MIME type: video/x-pn-realvideo (RV30/RV40 for RMVB), audio/x-pn-realaudio (Cook/ATRC). RMVB popular for Chinese fansub distribution (2003-2012).",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify '.RMF' at offset 0 (2E 52 4D 46)",
      "Read numHeaders at offset 14 (BE uint32) — typically 4-5",
      "PROP at offset 18: compare maxBitRate vs avgBitRate — large ratio confirms VBR",
      "MDPR objects: check MIME type for video/x-pn-realvideo (codec RV30/RV40)"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "RealPlayer",
    "VLC media player",
    "KMPlayer",
    "FFmpeg (rm demuxer)"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Video",
    "extensions": [".rmvb"],
    "relatedFormats": ["RM"],
    "note": "RMVB uses the identical RMFF container as .rm. The only format-level difference is VBR encoding (indicated in PROP flags and the large maxBitRate/avgBitRate ratio). RMVB dominated Asian online video in the 2000s; largely superseded by H.264/MP4."
  },
  "MimeTypes": [
